---
title: Sirloin Carne Asada Tacos with Southwest Crema and Pickled Shallot Salsa
description: There are few things more satisfying than steak for dinner. Until now! These carne-loaded tacos are hearty, filling, and most of all--delicious. Tender bites of seared steak are piled into warm tortillas along with a tangle of veggies, Southwest-spiced crema, and zingy pickled shallot—all topped off with a sprinkle of fresh cilantro. Taco’bout a weeknight win.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5d8a1ed92cb12059e9659f5c-a35ebd38.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/sirloin-carne-asada-tacos-5d8a1ed92cb12059e9659f5c-5f5969d9.pdf
author: Sara Heilman
cuisine: North America
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sirloin-carne-asada-tacos-5d8a1ed92cb12059e9659f5c
time required: 25 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 670 kcal
  fat: 27 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 50 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 41 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 1150 mg
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Wash and dry all produce. Core, deseed, and thinly slice @poblano pepper{1%unit}. Finely dice @Roma tomato{1%unit}. Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(leaves and stems chopped). Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1%unit}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine half the shallot, @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @sugar{1%teaspoon}, and @salt{}. Set aside, stirring occasionally.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, half the @southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon}, and a big pinch of salt. Stir in water @?water{1%tsp} at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add poblano and cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in remaining shallot and a big pinch of salt and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring, until lightly browned and softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a second medium bowl. Wipe out #pan.

Pat @diced steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan over high heat. Add steak and season with salt, pepper, and remaining southwest spice. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Return veggies to pan; stir until combined. Turn off heat.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6%unit} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}. (Alternatively, wrap tortillas in #foil{} and warm in a 425 degree oven for ~{5%minutes}.) Stir tomato into bowl with pickled shallot.

Divide steak mixture between tortillas. Top with salsa, crema, and cilantro. Serve.